<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Racial factions vs. Religious factions...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Garbonzo Darkbean aka Smoot">Garbonzo Darkbean aka Smoot</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:03 p.m. 15/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Racial factions vs. Religious factions...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1405" TARGET=_self>A GOOD QUESTION</A> (J'yzanon D'Örden)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>As an Erudite necro, I was unable to enter Neriak due to L'Crit, a 45+ NPC guard who hated Erudites. The entire city was closed off to me.

<P>I was also unable to enter Oggok or Grobb. KOS.
<P>Now, I was Agnostic, so I cannot be POSITIVE that the Trolls and Ogres wouldn't tolerate you if you worshipped an evil deity. But I'd wager against it.
<P>An Erudite Necro is one of THE most difficult characters to play. Your only "friends" are Erudite Necros (the human guild in Qeynos will not deal with Erudites) and the Freeport guild and vendors. Every place else is either KOS, or dubious.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
